@page "/custom-themes"
<PageTitle>Custom Themes - Saascade Docs</PageTitle>

<h1 id="custom-themes">Custom Themes</h1>

<div class="doc-layout">

<main class="documentation">

    <TechCard>
        <section class="card">

            <h2 id="built-in-custom-themes">Built-in Custom Themes</h2>

            <p class="subtitle">
                Saascade ships with several custom design systems that don't depend
                on any external CSS framework.
            </p>

            <hr />

            <h3>Basic1</h3>
            <pre><code>builder.Services.AddSingleton&lt;IDesignSystem&gt;(DesignSystems.Custom.Basic1);</code></pre>
            <p>A minimal custom design system with basic styling.</p>

            <h3>Handdrawn</h3>
            <p>Three handdrawn variants are available:</p>
            <ul>
                <li><strong>HanddrawnAssessible</strong> — accessible color palette with hand-drawn borders.</li>
                <li><strong>HanddrawnBlackAndWhite</strong> — monochrome hand-drawn aesthetic.</li>
                <li><strong>HanddrawnColor</strong> — colorful hand-drawn style.</li>
            </ul>

            <h3>Empty</h3>
            <pre><code>builder.Services.AddSingleton&lt;IDesignSystem&gt;(DesignSystems.Custom.EmptyDesignSystem);</code></pre>
            <p>A blank canvas — no classes applied. Useful for fully custom CSS.</p>

        </section>
    </TechCard>

    <TechCard>
        <section class="card">

            <h2 id="creating-your-own">Creating Your Own</h2>

            <p class="subtitle">
                You can implement IDesignSystem to build a fully custom design system
                that maps Saascade components to any class names you choose.
            </p>

            <hr />

            <p>
                See the Creating a Design System page for a step-by-step walkthrough.
                Custom design systems are registered the same way as the built-in ones
                and can return any stylesheet or JavaScript references your theme requires.
            </p>

        </section>
    </TechCard>

    <TechCard Tech="bootstrap">
        <section class="card">

            <h2 id="custom-themes-bootstrap">Bootstrap 5 Theming</h2>

            <p class="subtitle">Bootstrap 5 Custom Theming</p>

            <hr />

            <p>
                Bootstrap 5 supports Sass variable overrides and custom CSS properties for theming.
                When using Saascade with Bootstrap 5, you can customize colors, spacing, and
                typography by overriding Bootstrap's CSS custom properties or by providing a compiled
                Bootstrap build via GetStylesheetReferences in a custom design system class that
                extends the Bootstrap 5 preset.
            </p>

        </section>
    </TechCard>

    <TechCard Tech="daisyui">
        <section class="card">

            <h2 id="custom-themes-daisyui">DaisyUI Theming</h2>

            <p class="subtitle">DaisyUI Custom Theming</p>

            <hr />

            <p>
                DaisyUI has a built-in theme system driven by CSS custom properties. You can switch
                themes at runtime by changing the data-theme attribute on the html element. Custom
                DaisyUI themes are defined in your Tailwind configuration and automatically apply
                to all Saascade components without any code changes in the component layer.
            </p>

        </section>
    </TechCard>

    <TechCard Tech="basecoat">
        <section class="card">

            <h2 id="custom-themes-basecoat">Basecoat Theming</h2>

            <p class="subtitle">Basecoat Custom Theming</p>

            <hr />

            <p>
                Basecoat theming is done through Tailwind CSS configuration. You can extend or
                override the default Tailwind theme tokens — colors, fonts, spacing — in your
                tailwind.config.js file. Because Basecoat uses utility classes directly, custom
                theme tokens are immediately available to Saascade components through the
                Specialization and Class parameters.
            </p>

        </section>
    </TechCard>

</main>

<TableOfContents Items="@([
    new TocItem("custom-themes", "Custom Themes"),
    new TocItem("built-in-custom-themes", "Built-in Custom Themes", 2),
    new TocItem("creating-your-own", "Creating Your Own", 2),
    new TocItem("custom-themes-bootstrap", "Bootstrap 5 Theming", 2),
    new TocItem("custom-themes-daisyui", "DaisyUI Theming", 2),
    new TocItem("custom-themes-basecoat", "Basecoat Theming", 2)
])" />

</div>
